3
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:56,000
Jinny.

4
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:57,560
Wut,

5
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,240
stop.

6
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:02,640
PREVIOUSLY

7
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:03,960
I slept with another man.

8
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,319
I'm carrying his child.

9
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,240
Jinny!

10
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:07,440
Jinny!

11
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,880
Wut!

12
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:20,920
That's not true.

13
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,480
That's not true.

14
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:29,440
That's not true!

15
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:43,440
Wut, stop.

16
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,520
Stop right now. What are you doing?

17
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,520
Don't hurt my child.

18
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,480
If you're upset with me,

19
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:53,360
then take it out on me.

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,000
No.

21
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:57,840
Don't hurt him.

22
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,840
It's not his fault.

23
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,280
He's innocent.

24
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:07,000
Don't hurt him. He's your son.

25
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,640
No.

26
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:21,680
You said you cheated on me.

27
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:24,240
So how could he be mine? Stop lying.

28
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:27,160
Because you're like this.

29
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:31,280
When you lose your temper,

30
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,920
you hurt me.

31
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:37,800
I endured it all because I loved you.

32
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:40,640
But back then, I couldn't take it anymore.

33
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:47,920
I wanted to end things,
but you wouldn't let me.

34
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,760
The only way you'd ever let me go

35
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,040
was if I told you I was pregnant,

36
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:59,000
if I told you I cheated, so I made it up.

37
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:03,880
But I actually got pregnant
with your child. Do you understand now?

38
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,360
Then why didn't you come back to me?

39
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,240
Why did you leave me? Why?!

40
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:14,760
Because I didn't know if you could
take care of me and our child.

41
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:17,280
I came back secretly to check on you.

42
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,960
All I saw was you
getting drunk all the time,

43
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:22,240
<i>no job, no direction.</i>

44
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:24,680
<i>So why would I ever come back to you?!</i>

45
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:34,120
And how do I know that's really my child?

46
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,760
What if you're lying?

47
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,760
If you don't believe me,

48
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,640
just look at his face.

49
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:49,040
Look closely and
you'll see how much he looks like you.

50
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,920
Look.

51
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:54,040
Then you'll know whether I'm lying or not.

52
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,320
He's really my child?

53
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,720
Do you know

54
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,880
how hard it's been

55
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,920
to carry and raise a child alone?

56
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,960
But I made my choice.

57
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,880
No matter how hard it got,

58
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,720
I decided never to go back to you.

59
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,480
Have you even looked at yourself,

60
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:07,800
at how terrible you were?

61
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:14,600
I couldn't let my child grow up
with a father like that.

62
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:19,640
So I promised myself
I'd raise her the best I could

63
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,760
on my own.

64
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,000
I'm a mess.

65
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:32,040
I'm a failure. I'm sorry.

66
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,200
I'm sorry I wasn't a good boyfriend.

67
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:41,760
I'm sorry I wasn't a good father.
I'm sorry I…

68
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,560
I'm sorry too.

69
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:47,760
Sorry I never gave you
a chance to make things right.

70
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:52,760
Sorry I never told you honestly
what I really wanted.

71
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,440
It's my fault too.

72
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,640
I'm sorry, Wut.

73
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,680
Maybe this is how it's supposed to be.

74
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,240
Maybe I really didn't deserve you.

75
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,480
Please…

76
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,600
forgive me for everything.

77
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,480
Dad.

78
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,800
Go to Mom.

79
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,440
Alright?

80
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,400
Have a safe journey, Wut.

81
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,960
Goodbye.

82
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,800
Hearing their story,

83
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,040
it's hard not to feel sad, right?

84
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,080
Mm.

85
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,440
If he could really turn back time,

86
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,520
I think Wut would've tried to be better,

87
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,240
studied harder, worked harder.

88
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,640
And if Jinny had seen that,

89
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,880
maybe she'd have gone back to him.

90
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,720
They could've been a family again.

91
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:54,120
True. If things had gone differently,
Wut would probably be happy by now.

92
00:07:57,520 --> 00:08:00,840
But it's between the two of them.

93
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,880
We're outsiders.

94
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,400
We can't ever
really understand everything.

95
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,280
- Wow.
- No matter what,

96
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,520
we have no right to judge them anyway.

97
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:13,400
Look at you, talking like an old man.

98
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,360
An old wise man who's been through a lot.

99
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,160
I'm not old.

100
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:21,840
So, that means

101
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:23,920
the mission

102
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,760
is complete?

103
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,400
I think so. Right?

104
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:34,799
Then that means you will wake up, right?

105
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:38,520
I don't know.

106
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:42,720
But I really want to.

107
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,520
Yeah, me too.

108
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:53,000
I'm starting to get hungry.

109
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,640
Wanna grab something to eat?

110
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,160
Mm.

111
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:02,080
That place over there's still open.

112
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,440
Let's check it out.

113
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:08,200
Do they only sell coffee?

114
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,320
But at night?

115
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:14,600
They probably serve food too.

116
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,880
Let's look at the menu.

117
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:18,520
Let's see.

118
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:21,000
Uh, excuse me?

119
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,640
Anyone here?

120
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,840
No.

121
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,760
Only coffee here.

122
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,200
Have a seat.

123
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,360
So,

124
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,320
how was your first mission? Fun?

125
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,280
Did you learn anything

126
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:56,440
from what I made you do?

127
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,440
Well…

128
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,440
not really.

129
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:09,360
I hope their story

130
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:12,160
helps you understand
what life really means.

131
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:15,560
Everything that happens

132
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,760
has its reasons.

133
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:22,080
So whatever decisions you make,

134
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:25,040
you must be ready
to face the consequences.

135
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:29,880
And remember, a second chance

136
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,080
never comes easily.

137
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,040
But,

138
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,040
we completed the mission.

139
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:42,320
That means Alice can
go back to her body now, right?

140
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,120
Not yet.

141
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,480
Why are you sitting here?

142
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,120
Why not?

143
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:17,640
There are plenty of other tables.

144
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,200
Or you want me to sit even closer?

145
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:21,640
Hey, what's this?

146
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,080
- Even closer?
- Nana.

147
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:24,160
- Nana, move away.
- What?

148
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,400
- Hey.
- This close?

149
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,800
- What's this, Nana?
- No, no.

150
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,160
- Hey.
- Why? Are you shy?

151
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,120
- I'm not.
- What?

152
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,520
- Shy much?
- She leans in out of nowhere.

153
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,520
Nana.

154
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,760
- What?
- Back off.

155
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,000
- Why?
- He's blushing.

156
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,280
He can't even eat now.

157
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,400
- Aw, blushing, huh?
- Hm.

158
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:41,640
- Nana, seriously. Let's not do this.
- He's broken.

159
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,960
Are you actually blushing?

160
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,400
- Nana, seriously.
- Shy?

161
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,080
No. Back off.

162
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:47,920
Get off me.

163
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,400
- He's shy.
- Yeah, Punn likes it

164
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,520
- What?
- this way.

165
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,760
- You ruined the fun.
- Is this PunnNana couple?

166
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,160
Aah.

167
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,200
Want a bite?

168
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:03,120
Can I eat it instead?

169
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:08,200
Nana, no.

170
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:09,120
- Come on.
- Hey.

171
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,320
- Why?
- I feel like

172
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,600
the wind passes through my arm.

173
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:59,440
<i>I think of it every day</i>

174
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:02,640
<i>Every night</i>

175
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:06,440
<i>Wondering if someday</i>

176
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:09,440
<i>I'll be forgotten</i>

177
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:13,040
<i>We talk less</i>

178
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:16,280
<i>And less each day</i>

179
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,680
<i>Why have you</i>

180
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:23,720
<i>Changed so much?</i>

181
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,680
<i>I think, but I can't reach you</i>

182
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:33,240
<i>Think, think, but never reach you</i>

183
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:36,320
<i>I think, but I can't reach you</i>

184
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:40,280
<i>Think, think, but never reach you</i>

185
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:43,320
<i>Do you even know</i>

186
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:49,480
<i>Someone's suffering over you?</i>

187
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:51,760
<i>I just want to know</i>

188
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:55,600
<i>If our longing</i>

189
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:58,640
<i>Feels the same</i>

190
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:02,200
<i>Tell me truly</i>

191
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:05,560
<i>Has your heart changed?</i>

192
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:09,240
<i>It's not just me imagining</i>

193
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,520
<i>Right?</i>

194
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:16,640
<i>All the feelings I've been</i>

195
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,680
<i>Sending your way</i>

196
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:24,480
<i>They never reached you at all…</i>

197
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,160
Are you hungry?

198
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,200
Here.

199
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,960
Who'd you make that for?

200
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:54,920
Just

201
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,800
for someone passing by.

202
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,440
- Punn.
- Hm?

203
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,800
I'll show you something.

204
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:09,280
What is it?

205
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,640
How did you do that?

206
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:18,200
I just tried things.

207
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,320
Remember the other day

208
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,400
when I managed to push Joey?

209
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,960
Whoa, that's awesome.

210
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:27,480
Here you go.

211
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,080
So can you eat food now?

212
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:38,280
No, I can't. Just eat spiritually.

213
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:41,280
But when you cook for me,
it feels like I've eaten already.

214
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,520
Perfect. You've eaten,

215
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,680
so you can do the dishes, right?
I cooked for you.

216
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:50,440
Just kidding.

217
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,520
I'm full now.

218
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:54,840
Already?

219
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:03,280
<i>It's been so long since we met</i>
<i>Do you miss me?</i>

220
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:07,160
<i>It's been so long since we met</i>
<i>Do you still think of me?</i>

221
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:11,240
<i>Whoa-oh-oh, how much I miss you</i>

222
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:14,240
<i>I don't know what's on your mind</i>

223
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:16,040
<i>But I miss you like crazy</i>

224
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,720
It's not working.

225
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:24,800
Hm.

226
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:30,360
<i>Where's Nana gone?</i>

227
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:33,120
She's skipped practice for days.

228
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:35,680
I've messaged her a bunch,

229
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,040
no reply, not read.

230
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,840
You think we'll even be ready?
The show's coming up soon.

231
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:44,120
And you. You're the band leader.

232
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,240
Don't you care about your members?

233
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,920
We'll ask her

234
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,600
when we see her at school.

235
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,880
She didn't come today either.

236
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,720
- How do you know?
- Well.

237
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:58,600
She always eats with us.

238
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:03,000
Maybe she went with other friends.
You think she doesn't have any?

239
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:06,480
Don't know.
I've never seen her with anyone.

240
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:09,319
When she auditioned for our band,

241
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,040
that was the first time
I saw her at school.

242
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:12,880
Maybe she just transferred recently.

243
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,520
Ugh.

244
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:16,520
Stop arguing back and forth.

245
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,240
What's with you, Joey?

246
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:22,160
You're always talking to Nana.

247
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,480
You don't know what's going on with her?

248
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,200
No idea.

249
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,040
Hm.

250
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,640
BOMBAY: DOES ANYONE KNOW NANA?

251
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:56,240
What? This is mine now.

252
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,440
You're just eating too slowly. I got it.

253
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:00,520
- It's good.
- You care more about food.

254
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,640
Can you help me check her posts instead?

255
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,160
- What?
- Here.

256
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,720
Alright.

257
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,040
You're just not popular.

258
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,880
Fine,

259
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:27,480
- you do it then.
- I can't.

260
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:29,240
All my girls will misunderstand.

261
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:32,640
Nonsense.

262
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:39,880
BAS: SHE'S ALWAYS WITH YOU GUYS.
ISN'T SHE YOUR FRIEND?

263
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:45,920
- Isn't it weird?
- I don't know.

264
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,320
<i>Hello.</i>

265
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

266
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:53,080
Um, I came to ask about a student.

267
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:56,080
She hasn't come to class for several days.

268
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:58,480
- Mm.
- Can we know her address?

269
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,040
Her name's Nana.

270
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:04,960
We'll need her full name,
class, and grade, please.

271
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,360
You know that?

