What class is she in?

273
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,640
Hey, have you seen her before?

274
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,800
- No, doesn't look familiar.
- Not at all?

275
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,000
Not familiar at all?

276
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:16,800
I've never seen her.

277
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:17,960
No.

278
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:20,400
We've got her ID now.

279
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:21,920
Punn.

280
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,000
How did you get that?

281
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,800
I went to find this copy.

282
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,200
Where did you even get it from?

283
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:29,080
I'll tell you later.

284
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:33,840
There's no record
of this student in our school.

285
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:36,480
<i>I told you.</i>

286
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:38,040
I guarantee

287
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:39,920
she's a ghost who loves music.

288
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,600
She disguised herself to join us.

289
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:47,600
What the hell?

290
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,080
Alright, this evening,

291
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:51,880
let's go find her.

292
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,480
You know where she lives?

293
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:56,960
Of course.

294
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:01,920
- Oh.
- Here.

295
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,400
IDENTIFICATION CARD

296
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:06,320
This is the place.

297
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,400
- Let's ring the bell.
- Mm.

298
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,080
Nana!

299
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,320
- Nana!
- Why are you yelling?

300
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:22,680
Then how's she gonna come out?

301
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:25,240
She didn't even respond to the doorbell.

302
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,120
You're too loud.

303
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,600
What are you guys doing here?

304
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,440
How did you know this is my house?

305
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:11,320
Can you drop the attitude?
We're worried about you.

306
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,680
What are you talking about?

307
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:17,080
You guys wouldn't understand my life.
Just go.

308
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:19,320
If you weren't serious about the band,

309
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,760
why audition in the first place?

310
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:24,320
You wanted in so badly,

311
00:21:25,040 --> 00:21:26,320
and now that you got in,

312
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,040
you're acting like this?

313
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:30,880
If you wanna quit, fine,

314
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,720
but at least tell us why.

315
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,720
Hey, what the hell?

316
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:37,960
She can't quit now.
The show's in a few days.

317
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:40,120
And if she leaves, who'll replace her?

318
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,960
We'll make it work with whoever's left.

319
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,760
We just want to know

320
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,680
what happened.

321
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:48,600
Maybe we can help.

322
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:49,600
Nana.

323
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:52,600
We're worried about you.

324
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:56,920
Even if we might've been harsh sometimes,

325
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:59,560
we all genuinely care about you.

326
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:01,000
If there's something wrong,

327
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,840
something bothering you,

328
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:04,760
can you tell us?

329
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:09,840
Well…

330
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:13,400
My mom's really sick.
Her condition's gotten worse.

331
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:15,680
And I don't have any money.

332
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:18,680
I've been working to pay for rent

333
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,800
and all the other expenses.

334
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:25,440
Should we talk inside
if it's gonna take a while?

335
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,560
You're in the way.

336
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:34,720
Just go home.
I need to take care of my mom.

337
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,600
Wait, wait. Hey.

338
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:40,280
Are you free tomorrow?
Or are you working somewhere?

339
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,560
We can come talk with you there.

340
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:44,520
Is that okay?

341
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,360
Yeah, I'll send you the address.

342
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:16,040
Mom, I'm home.

343
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,200
I bought congee for you today.

344
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:31,920
Do you want to eat now?
I'll put it in a bowl.

345
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:54,520
If you're not hungry yet,
you can rest first.

346
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,560
When we went to Nana's house,

347
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,080
did you see anyone?

348
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:36,600
Yeah.

349
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:42,200
I saw an old, skinny woman

350
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,960
walking slowly in the kitchen.

351
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:49,680
I think Nana's hiding something.

352
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:51,800
Let's ask her tomorrow.

353
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,920
But go easy on her, okay?

354
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:58,160
I think…

355
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:01,200
for some people,

356
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:04,200
some things are really hard to talk about.

357
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:16,680
Why kitchen though?

358
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:19,200
<i>So?</i>

359
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,760
Are you quitting the band?

360
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,760
Don't quit.

361
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,560
You can't. There's no time left.

362
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,640
Well…

363
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:37,280
My mom's been in the last stage of cancer
for a while now.

364
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:40,240
All our savings

365
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:43,000
are used for her treatments.

366
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:48,600
I've had to work to pay the rent,

367
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,520
because there's no way
I can move her out anymore.

368
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,920
Wait, let me ask you this first.

369
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,680
You're not a student from our school?

370
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,640
Mm.

371
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:04,720
That's right.

372
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:09,280
I dropped out a year ago.

373
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:12,320
I had to work to earn money.

374
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,920
I take any job I can find,

375
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:18,680
then go home and care for my mom,
back and forth like that.

376
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,360
If she's hospitalized,

377
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:26,360
I have to take time off.

378
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:31,080
<i>I saw your audition poster</i>
<i>on the practice room board.</i>

379
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,560
<i>I really wanted to join.</i>

380
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:36,000
<i>But it seemed more convenient</i>
<i>if I applied as your school's student,</i>

381
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:37,640
<i>so I applied anyway.</i>

382
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:39,880
<i>That day, we didn't need uniforms.</i>

383
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:42,760
<i>But before I could even play,</i>
<i>the event got canceled.</i>

384
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:46,920
I used to rent this studio sometimes,
back when I could still afford it.

385
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,280
But lately,

386
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:51,880
I haven't come at all.

387
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:56,160
So I figured I might as well quit.

388
00:26:57,760 --> 00:27:00,920
There's one way, though.

389
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:04,240
We could still play and earn money.

390
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:09,120
If we find a café that hires us,

391
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:11,360
we'd still get to play together

392
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,680
and get paid too.

393
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:16,520
But would they even take us?

394
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:20,840
We're just newbies.
Our skills are barely okay.

395
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,680
Wait.

396
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:28,080
I just remembered.
My friend sent me a post yesterday.

397
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:30,440
There's this café
looking for school bands to play.

398
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:32,640
- Here.
- Let me see.

399
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:36,840
BAND WANTED AT DREAM CAFE
A CHANCE TO SHOWCASE AND GET PAID

400
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:40,640
<i>It's been so long since we met</i>
<i>Do you miss me?</i>

401
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:42,760
<i>It's been so long since we met</i>

402
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:45,040
<i>Do you still think of me?</i>

403
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:47,400
<i>Whoa-oh-oh</i>

404
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:49,240
<i>How much I miss you</i>

405
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:52,520
<i>I'll show you just how much</i>

406
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:55,480
<i>Hug you tight, kiss your cheek</i>

407
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:57,600
<i>So you'll know how much I've missed you</i>

408
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:59,120
<i>I'll shout out loud</i>

409
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,800
<i>Just how much I miss you</i>

410
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:05,520
<i>Whoa-oh-oh, I miss you so bad</i>

411
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:08,280
<i>I don't know what's on your mind</i>

412
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:11,040
<i>But I miss you like crazy</i>

413
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:24,040
I told you we'd pass.

414
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,760
- See? Cheers!
- Cheers!

415
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:30,240
Hey, we won't need
my studio anymore, right?

416
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:32,840
- We'll still need it.
- Oh.

417
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:35,760
Hey, I should head home.

418
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:38,440
- Hm, wait.
- Wait.

419
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:40,360
Let's talk first.

420
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:41,440
Mm.

421
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,160
So,

422
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:45,680
the payment for playing at the café

423
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:49,200
isn't much, but

424
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:51,600
it's something.

425
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:54,200
I thought…

426
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,600
I'll give all the money from this gig

427
00:29:00,360 --> 00:29:01,960
to you, Nana.

428
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:07,040
It won't be a lot, I know.

429
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,880
So I'm adding some of my own savings too.

430
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,360
At least it'll help
with your rent for now.

431
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:18,720
Don't worry about it. I'm the band leader.

432
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:22,520
If anyone's struggling,
I've gotta support them.

433
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:26,920
Once I pick our members,
it's my job to keep them.

434
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,280
Here.

435
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:30,960
Thank you.

436
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,280
- Come on, eat first, eat first.
- Yeah, I'm starving.

437
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,760
Why didn't he transfer the money?

438
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:39,400
Let's keep eating.

439
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,200
I gotta go now.

440
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:44,960
Now?

441
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:48,200
See you later.

442
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:50,000
Hey, wait.

443
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,600
She didn't even finish hers.

444
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:55,920
You want it?

445
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,080
What, you'll eat it?

446
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,600
Here's your take-home.

447
00:29:58,680 --> 00:29:59,840
Thank you.

448
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:03,160
- What's so funny?
- So good.

449
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,680
- It's delicious.
- Yeah.

450
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:10,400
I brought wontons for you.

451
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,560
I'm sorry I'm home late tonight.

452
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:06,400
Punn.

453
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:08,640
Punn.

454
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:11,560
Oh!

455
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:12,960
Whoa.

456
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:16,560
What's wrong? Why are you in such a rush?

457
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,120
Well…

458
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:26,680
Nana's mom's dead.

459
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:28,560
What?

460
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:33,480
How's Nana?

461
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,800
I'll text everyone.

462
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:38,680
No. It's…

463
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:43,000
Nana's mom

464
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:46,160
didn't just die.

465
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:51,440
Her body's decomposing.

466
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,200
I don't think

467
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:57,960
Nana's okay.

468
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:00,440
What do we do?

469
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:04,280
I don't know

470
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:07,000
what she's thinking, how she's feeling.

471
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:10,400
But if you guys
try to go into her house again,

472
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,560
it might not be good.

473
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:18,240
So what's our plan?

474
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:24,800
Should we call rescue services, secretly?

475
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,440
I don't think that's a good idea.

476
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,600
We should talk to her.
Help her understand.

477
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:35,240
She's probably

478
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:37,320
really fragile right now.

479
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,880
Let's talk it through together tomorrow.

480
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:45,040
I didn't think about that.

481
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:53,480
That Nana.

482
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:55,960
She's such a liar.

483
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:57,840
Hey.

484
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,720
Don't be too hard on her.

485
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:02,360
I think she still has things
she hasn't told us yet.

486
00:33:02,880 --> 00:33:05,960
But keeping a corpse in the house,

487
00:33:06,480 --> 00:33:07,880
that's serious.

488
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:10,240
Anyway, how did you even find out?

489
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:12,280
I just did, okay?

490
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:14,800
You always do this.

491
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:18,760
Like when you got Nana's ID.
How did you even get it?

492
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,640
You haven't told us.

493
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:23,600
Right, I forgot to explain.

494
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:26,760
I once saw Nana going into a bookstore,

495
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:30,520
so I figured she might be a member there.

496
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:34,480
I had to make up this whole story

497
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:36,480
before the owner
finally gave me that copy.

498
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:40,840
So, when are you going to
meet and talk again?

499
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:44,800
Or should we wait
until after the café performance?

500
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:46,480
But…

501
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:49,080
by then, I think

502
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:52,400
her mom's body might already be rotting.

503
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,520
Let's just act normal

504
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,600
for tonight,

505
00:33:58,560 --> 00:33:59,840
- okay?
- Okay.

506
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,120
Okay.

507
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:18,800
- One dry noodle and one wonton soup to go.
- Sure thing.

508
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:34,840
Nana, how's your mom?

509
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:43,400
Still the same.
I don't know how many days she's got left.

510
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:45,199
Oh.

511
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:49,440
Then, can I come visit her sometime?

512
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:51,960
After the competition's over, okay?

513
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:54,199
It's only three days away.

514
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:57,760
Let's finish the competition first.

515
00:34:58,400 --> 00:34:59,680
Mm.

516
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:04,320
Then I'll go now.

517
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:09,920
Wait.

518
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:14,760
Didn't you order noodles to go?

519
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:17,080
Oh.

520
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:18,960
Right.

521
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:44,920
Mom,

522
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:47,280
come eat the wontons, okay?

523
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,720
Are you bored of them?

524
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:51,720
It's the same as yesterday.

525
00:36:36,120 --> 00:36:37,520
Come eat with me.

526
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:41,040
It's okay. I already ate.

527
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:44,800
Sit here, then.

528
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,960
Nana's a good girl, isn't she?

529
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:05,880
Yes.

530
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:09,400
She's a wonderful daughter
and a good friend too.

531
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:12,880
I don't want to go.

532
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:19,160
I don't want to leave her alone.

533
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,680
Ma'am.

534
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:25,040
Nana has to report this now.

535
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:29,240
If she keeps your body at home any longer,

536
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:32,800
she could get into trouble.

537
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,800
If no one comes in,

538
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,240
no one will know.

539
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:42,160
You have to let her go.

540
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:45,200
Don't you want to see her graduate?

541
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:48,960
Right now, Nana had to drop out

542
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:51,840
to work and pay
all the household expenses.

543
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:56,280
Can you let her go?

544
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:59,200
We've been doing fine

545
